<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="point-n">point <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /pɔɪnt/    美 /pɔɪnt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-c">1.★ <strong>[C] 尖端；点；小数点：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the point of a pencil / knife 
铅笔尖/刀尖</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The two lines cross at point C. 
这两条线在C点相交。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>two point six 
二点六(2.6)</p></div>

<h4 id="2-c">2.★ <strong>[C] 时间点；地点；（发展的）阶段；程度； 地步：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>a turning / starting point</strong>
转折点/起点</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>a low / high point</strong>
低谷/巅峰</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You’ll regret <strong>at some point</strong> in the future if you don’t study hard today.
如果你现在不好好学习，将来某个时候你就会后悔。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I have <strong>reached a point</strong> in my life when / where I am supposed to make decisions of my own.
我到了人生中应该自己拿主意的时候。</p><footer>2009 浙江</footer></div>

<h4 id="3-c">3.★ <strong>[C] 观点；要点；特点：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Whenever you buy a present, you should think about it <strong>from</strong> the receiver’s <strong>point of view</strong>.
每当你买礼物时，都应当从接受者的角度来考虑。</p><footer>2014 湖南</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The language use is good and the main points are covered.
（文章的）语言运用很好，并涵盖了主要内容。</p><footer>2020 全国</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You didn’t intend to be late. But <strong>that’s not the point</strong> (= not the important thing).
你不想迟到，但那不是重点。</p><footer>2014 辽宁</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He told a story, within which he tried to <strong>make</strong> his <strong>point</strong>.
故事中他提出了自己的观点。</p><footer>2015 湖北</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Next time you visit Bob, remember to give him a call in advance.
下次你去拜访鲍勃时，记得事 先给他打个电话。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Good point. I will.
好主意。我会的。</p><footer>2020 天津</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>strong / weak points</strong>
强项/不足处</p></div>

<h4 id="4-c">4.★ <strong>[C] (比赛或运动中的)分 (数)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>win a match by ten points to three 
以10比3赢得比赛</p></div>

<h4 id="5-u">5.★ <strong>[U] 意图；目的；理由</strong></h4>
<p>the purpose or aim of sth：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>What’s the point</strong> of forcing him to do what he is unwilling to? 
强迫他做不愿意做的事情有什么意义呢?</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>There’s no point in</strong> getting angry. 
生气是没有用的。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="high-point">high point</h3>
<p>1.<strong>最有意思（或最令人愉快、最好）的部分</strong>  </p>
<h3 id="make-a-point-of-doing-sth">make a point of doing sth</h3>
<p>1.<strong>(即使费力也) 特意做某事：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He made a point of spending Saturdays with his children. 
星期六他必定要和孩子们在一起。</p></div>

<h3 id="on-the-point-of">on the point of</h3>
<p>1.<strong>正要…的时候：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She was on the point of going out when the telephone rang. 
她正要出去，电话铃响了。</p></div>

<h3 id="to-the-point">to the point</h3>
<p>1.<strong>中肯的；切题的：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Your advice is very much to the point.
你的建议很中肯。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I wish you’d <strong>get to the point</strong> (= talk about the most important thing).
我希望你能切入正题。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>What’s the point, in your opinion, <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ helping him if he doesn’t make an effort to help himself?  （2011 江西改）  </li>
<li>I like Mr Miner’s speech; it was clear and <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ the point.   （2008 辽宁改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. of  2. to   </p></div>